its value thus is twofold : as a biography for welles fans , and as a history of film industry operations and politics . mention the name orson welles and his most famous involvement - with the radio scare 'war of the worlds ' - immediately comes to mind ; but for a deeper understanding of welles ' life and career you need what ever happened to orson welles ? : a portrait of an independent career . his later projects were largely self-financed and erratically distributed , but film critic and biographer joseph mcbride has a personal familiarity with welles from previous projects worked on with him and here shows how the hollywood studio system forced welles out of the industry . its value thus is twofold : as a biography for welles fans , and as a history of film industry operations and politics . diane c. donovan california bookwatc